'''Nathan "Moraj_Markinnison" Larkins''' (July, [[1982]] – October, [[2002]]) was a beta tester of [[Sony|Sony Online Entertainment's]] [[Roleplaying game|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies|Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided]]''.

==Biography==
When Nathan Larkins died as a result of a car wreck<ref name="Guinness">''Guinness World Records 2008: Gamer's Edition''. Time Home Entertainment, Inc. {{ISBN|978-1-904-99421-3}}.</ref> in early October of [[2002]],<ref name="Memorial">{{WebCite|url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/80371733/nathan-larkins|text=Nathan Larkins|date=2011-11-13|work=[[Wikipedia:Find a Grave|Find a Grave]]|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/Pbs5x}}</ref> the ''[[Star Wars Galaxies|Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided]]'' team placed a [[Moraj Memorial]] flag outside the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Bestine (city)/Legends|Bestine]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] to honor his dedication to the [[Star Wars video games|game]] and the community. The flag marked the location where the beta testers entered the [[Star Wars video games|game]],<ref name="Guinness" /> and provided an [[in-universe]] description in memory of the "brave [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Moraj]]."<ref name="AED" /> This was recognized by the [[Wikipedia:Guinness World Records|''Guinness World Records'']] as the earliest virtual memorial ever included in an [[Roleplaying game|MMORPG]], as first noted in an entry of the ''Guinness World Records 2008: Gamer's Edition''.<ref name="Guinness" />

An online memorial page for Nathan highlights his valued history as a member of the beta test community, including his membership in a guild known as The Crescent Order, and as a beloved participant of the Newbie Welcome Wagon (NWW).<ref name="Memorial" /> With the release of ''Star Wars Galaxies'' in [[2003]], [[Maroj Melon]]s were included as a starting item for players of the game. However, unlike the historical marker near Bestine, the game did not clearly indicate whether these [[Melon/Legends|melons]] were intended to be yet another tribute to Nathan Larkins (note the slight transposition of letters between Maroj and Moraj).<ref name="AED" />

